# UI Component Governance

Use existing primitives from `components/ui/*` first. Prefer composition over creating new shared primitives.

## Reuse-First Workflow

1. Before building UI, check whether the needed primitive already exists in `components/ui/*`.
2. If it exists, use it directly or compose it in `features/<feature>/components/*`.
3. Do not create a new file in `components/ui/*` when an existing primitive can satisfy the requirement.

## New Primitive Gate

Create a new shared primitive in `components/ui/*` only when all are true:

- No existing component can cover the requirement without hacks.
- The need is reusable across multiple features/pages.
- You explicitly ask for confirmation before creating the new primitive.

When confirmation is needed, ask:
"No suitable existing `components/ui/*` primitive found. Do you want me to create a new shared component in `components/ui/`?"

## Neo Drive vs Primitives

- Drive-specific layouts (sidebar, dashboard cards, explorer toolbar) belong in `features/drive/` or `components/layout/`, not new `components/ui/*` files.
- Shared table styling uses `components/ui/table.tsx` (`TableContainer`, `TableSortHead`, etc.) — see `docs/TABLE_BEHAVIOR_GUIDE.md`.
- Drive colors/spacing: `docs/DRIVE_UI_GUIDE.md` and `.drive-shell` tokens in `app/globals.css`.

## Styling and Consistency

- Keep theme consistency by using existing tokens, variants, and utility patterns.
- Avoid one-off visual systems or duplicate component APIs.
- Prefer updating existing variants over introducing near-duplicate primitives.
